OL,3,CIndecent exposure on the rise as
OL,4,Cvictims claim it's too often dismissed
OL,6,F"An incident which lasted 20 minutes
OL,7,Fimpacted my life for the next 50
OL,8,Fyears."
OL,10,FThose are the harrowing words one
OL,11,Fsurvivor of exposure told me during an
OL,12,Femotionally-charged interview.
OL,14,FThe crime of exposure, commonly known
OL,15,Fas indecent exposure, is when someone
OL,16,Fintentionally exposes their genitals
OL,17,Fintending for another person to see
OL,18,Fthem and feel alarm or distress.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
