PN,46202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1778842974
OL,3,CIndecent exposure on the rise as
OL,4,Cvictims claim it's too often dismissed
OL,6,FExclusive data obtained by ITV Wales
OL,7,Fshows exposure is on the rise. In
OL,8,F2024, there were 642 reports made,
OL,9,Fcompared to 567 in 2023.
OL,11,FWhat many dismiss as merely
OL,12,F'flashing', for victims can leave deep
OL,13,Fpsychological scars.
OL,15,FDavid, not his real name, told me he
OL,16,Fwas subjected to indecent exposure
OL,17,Fwhen he was just seven years old.
OL,19,FNow aged 60, he reflected on how the
OL,20,Fimpact of that incident shaped his
OL,21,Flife for half a century.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1778842974
OL,3,CIndecent exposure on the rise as
OL,4,Cvictims claim it's too often dismissed
OL,6,FHe said: "The feelings at the time
OL,7,Fwere pure terror. Like an out of body
OL,8,Fexperience because of the nature of
OL,9,Fwhat was happening. It was horrific."
OL,11,FWhat began as exposure, for David,
OL,12,Fescalated into more serious sexual
OL,13,Fviolence.
OL,15,FHe fears that a 'flippant' outlook on
OL,16,Fexposure could lead to others
OL,17,Fexperiencing similar trauma.
OL,19,F"I think in society it should be taken
OL,20,Fmuch more seriously than it is
OL,21,Fpresently. It's not a joke."
OL,26,@nD@JOUqD@eO]{D@AOU}D@\O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/12
