CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1778842974
OL,3,CIndecent exposure on the rise as
OL,4,Cvictims claim it's too often dismissed
OL,6,FFor Anna, whose name has been changed
OL,7,Fto protect her identity, the incident
OL,8,Fis still raw.
OL,10,FShe was walking home from a friend's
OL,11,Fhouse at 8pm in January 2025, when she
OL,12,Fnoticed a man walking closely behind
OL,13,Fher.
OL,15,F"I passed a man who had his back
OL,16,Fturned to the main busy road. A minute
OL,17,For two later, I saw his shadow
OL,18,Ffollowing pretty closely behind me. It
OL,19,Fwas a bit like a horror film.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1778842974
OL,3,CIndecent exposure on the rise as
OL,4,Cvictims claim it's too often dismissed
OL,6,F"That's when I felt him tap me on the
OL,7,Fshoulder. I quickly turned around. He
OL,8,Ftook a few steps towards me and
OL,9,Fexposed himself to me."
OL,11,FAlthough she was in 'utter shock', she
OL,12,Fsaid she had 'no option' but to 'kick
OL,13,Fhim away' as he had blocked her path.
OL,15,F"I felt violated. I was really
OL,16,Fdistressed. When I got home, I just
OL,17,Fcried because I didn't know what to
OL,18,Fdo."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1778842974
OL,3,CIndecent exposure on the rise as
OL,4,Cvictims claim it's too often dismissed
OL,6,FThe police told Anna that four other
OL,7,Fwomen had also been assaulted by the
OL,8,Fsame man that night, however due to
OL,9,F'investigative and evidential
OL,10,Fdifficulties' the case could not be
OL,11,Fprogressed.
OL,13,FShe said: "I just keep thinking he's
OL,14,Fprobably still out there repeating the
OL,15,Fsame behaviour to other people. The
OL,16,Fpolice had seemed quite on it,
OL,17,Finitially. I felt a glimmer of hope. I
OL,18,Fdid feel really let down."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
